items.name: CynkyAutomation
items.description: Powered by Selenium, Specflow and ML.Net with detailed HTML reporting, Machine Learning Analysis and Logging capabilities - CynkyAutomation framework can handle any website that is built using AJAX, React, AngularJS, Vue.js, Single Page Applications, Salesforce, Dynamics 365 CRM and many more.

items.name: Diabetes-Prediction-ML-Web-App
items.description: Diabetes Prediction ML Web App. Includes machine learning models such as Logistic Regression, Random Forest, Gradient Boosting, and Support Vector Machine (SVM). For Web App - HTML, CSS and Django framework.

items.name: scikit-learn_bench
items.description: scikit-learn_bench benchmarks various implementations of machine learning algorithms across data analytics frameworks. It currently support the scikit-learn, DAAL4PY, cuML, and XGBoost frameworks for commonly used machine learning algorithms.

items.description: iQuanta is a Python module designed to establish an innovative framework for quantifying the information content within neural data by leveraging machine learning techniques.

items.description: Implementation of Data-mining and Machine learning algorithms from Scratch and using Frameworks as well

items.description: A framework to serve various generative AIs and other machine learning functions via WebSocket and JSONRPC.

items.name: apax
items.description: A flexible and performant framework for training machine learning potentials.

items.name: End-to-end-ML-System-Benchmark
items.description: A modular suite for benchmarking all stages of Machine Learning pipelines. To find bottlenecks in such pipelines and compare different ML tools, this framework can calculate and visualize several metrics in the data preparation, model training, model validation and inference stages.

items.name: streamingAD_extendedframework
items.description: Extended framework for machine learning models in streaming anomaly detection

items.name: DeepMol
items.description: DeepMol: A Machine and Deep Learning Framework for Computational Chemistry

items.name: ML-project
items.description: The MNIST dataset is a widely used collection of handwritten digits, serving as a benchmark for various machine learning tasks. This project aims to leverage the Tensorflow framework and the Scikit-Learn library to explore and implement both K-Nearest Neighbors (K-NN) and Artificial Neural Network (ANN) algorithms .

items.name: ENFusion
items.description: A machine learning fusion framework for classification audio recordings utilizing ENF signals

items.name: Cotton-Plant-Disease-Detection-
items.description: CottonPlantDiseaseDetection is a comprehensive machine learning project aimed at predicting diseases in cotton plants to assist farmers in crop management. The repository encompasses a robust framework for disease classification leveraging state-of-the-art machine learning algorithms and image processing techniques.

items.name: zignition
items.description: Simple machine learning framework. Used to learn neural network architectures and delve into the fundamentals.

items.name: FinML
items.description: FinML: A Practical Machine Learning Framework for Dynamic Stock Selection

items.description: Framework for solving discrete optimization problems using a combination of Mixed-Integer Linear Programming (MIP) and Machine Learning (ML)

items.name: NeuralMachineTranslationModel
items.description: Implemented two neural machine translation (NMT) models using different deep learning frameworks: TensorFlow/Keras and PyTorch.

items.name: minitorch
items.description: A machine learning framework written from scratch for educational purposes. Inspired by PyTorch and tinygrad.

items.name: niceml
items.description: niceML  is a Python-based MLOps framework designed to streamline the development and maintenance of machine learning projects, offering efficient and scalable pipelines using TensorFlow and Dagster.

items.name: plant_phenotyping_machine_learning_application
items.description: a plant phenotyping machine learning with defacto implementation of three machine learning frameworks and allows for the scalable management of the plant pheotyping data and also for the selection of the traits and the machine learning classifiers. it will also allows for the cusotmization of the machine learning models.

items.name: edspdf
items.description: EDS-PDF is a generic, pure-Python framework for text extraction from PDF documents. It provides the machinery to use rule- or machine-learning-based approaches to classify text blocs between body and meta-data.

items.name: Optimising-Transaction-Schedules-
items.description: Implementing a quantum machine learning model to estimate the optimal transaction schedule.  Tech stack and Frameworks : Qiskit, Pytourch , IBM Quantum Composer, VQC
